{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b11ab002-eb2f-432d-960c-6bdaa9d05e93","content":"For a **web API project**, here are your main options:\n\n### Templates\n| Template | Command |\n|---|---|\n| ASP.NET Core Web API | `dotnet new webapi` |\n| ASP.NET Core Minimal API | `dotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis` |\n| ASP.NET Core API (controllers) | `dotnet new webapi --use-controllers` |\n\n### Authentication Options (`--auth`)\n| Value | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (org) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --use-controllers -o MyApi\n```\n\nYou can also add **JWT Bearer** auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need a custom identity provider. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` for all available flags.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ba19250b-2db0-4101-a4cf-780b8467f2fa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context) or possibly other frameworks. Let me answer based on my knowledge without needing to search the codebase, since this is a general development question.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"403C:1ECF:65F2939:7236D75:69EC0DF4"},"id":"346c49c4-e242-4057-8f6f-b977f5ff88f2","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:36.687Z","parentId":"b110e2b5-a442-4fd1-88df-a1754c4fea78"}
